🎯 Root Cause

Even though:

sysadmin is in sys_protected group ✅

File exists and is executable ✅


👉 The .CREDENTIAL binary requires elevated privileges (root) to read the encrypted keyring.

So:

OS_PASSWORD=`/opt/platform/.keyring/.../.CREDENTIAL`

fails silently → results in:

OS_PASSWORD=


---

✅ Fix (Correct & Standard in StarlingX)

🔥 Use sudo -E when sourcing openrc

Run this:

sudo -E bash -c "source /etc/platform/openrc && system host-list"

👉 This works because:

sudo allows .CREDENTIAL to execute properly

-E preserves environment variables



